  "text": "TLRs are PRRs that can recognize certain DAMPs and promote activation and migration of cDCs to LNs. Self-DNA stimulates signaling via TLR9 when delivered to endosomal compartments in DCs. [CITATION_1] To determine whether TLR9 was involved in the effects of DNA on cDC migration and activation, we treated WT or TLR9KO mice with AF647-ova þ beryllium and followed the accumulation of AF647-Ova þ cDCs in the LDLNs 48 h later. The total numbers of cDCs accumulating in the LDLNs of TLR9KO mice were reduced compared with WT mice (Figure 5c ). However, AF647-Ova þ cDCs in the LDLNs of beryllium-exposed WT and TLR9KO mice expressed similar levels of CD80 and CD86 (Figure 5d ). Thus TLR9 may recognize DNA and contribute to the observed effects on DC migration, but other pathways contribute to optimal upregulation of costimulatory molecules on cDCs in the draining LN.",
